{"questionId":"12242","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Show that <strong><em>M</em> </strong>is non-singular.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>finding det<strong><em> M </em></strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = {a^2} + {b^2}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{a^2} + {b^2} > 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>, therefore <strong><em>M</em></strong> is non-singular or equivalent statement&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12242","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.29a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that M is non-singular.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}